list.item:
Are receiving Hepatitis C drug combinations containing ombitasvir/paritaprevir/ritonavir, with or without dasabuvir, due to the potential for ALT elevations (see Warnings ,
RISK OF LIVER ENZYME ELEVATIONS WITH CONCOMITANT HEPATITIS CTREATMENT
)

text.paragraph:
During clinical trials with the Hepatitis C combination drug regimen that contains ombitasvir/paritaprevir/ritonavir, with or without dasabuvir, ALT elevations greater than 5 times the upper limit of normal (ULN), including some cases greater than 20 times the ULN, were significantly more frequent in women using ethinyl estradiol-containing medications such as COCs. Discontinue PIMTREATM prior to starting therapy with the combination drug regimen ombitasvir/paritaprevir/ritonavir, with or without dasabuvir (see 
                              CONTRAINDICATIONS
                           ). PIMTREATM can be restarted approximately 2 weeks following completion of treatment with the combination drug regimen.
